The article discusses the comprehensive response and commitment of the U.S. government to address the border security issues between the U.S. and Mexico. The President is concerned about the increased violence in cities like Ciudad Juarez and Tijuana and the impact it has on both sides of the border. The U.S. is working with Mexico to support their campaign against violent cartels and reduce contraband. The Merida Initiative involves investing $700 million in law enforcement and judicial capacity in Mexico. Efforts are being made to disrupt illegal flows of weapons and cash to Mexico and to ensure border security. The U.S. is also working with Mexico to confront criminal enterprises responsible for violence and drug trafficking. Additionally, efforts are being made to cut off funding for Mexican drug cartels and reduce the demand for illegal drugs within the U.S.